text: Elizabeth Anne Cutler FRS FBA ( - ) was an Australian psycholinguist. She was the director emeritus of the Max Planck Institute for Psycholinguistics until 2012. Cutler was elected to fellowships of the Royal Society, the British Academy, and the Academy of the Social Sciences in Australia during her career. She was elected a member of the Academia Europaea in 1999. She was a professor at Western Sydney University. ==References== Category:1945 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Australian academics Category:Australian linguists Category:Psychologists Category:Scientists from Victoria (Australia) Category:People from Sydney Category:Members of Academia Europaea
